What is String??
A String in Java is a sequence of characters used to store text, enclosed by double quotes
for eg:
"Hello" => is a String
String is immutable in java.
immutable=>Immutable means cannot be changed after it is created.
for eg:
public class Example {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String name = "Java";

        name.concat(" Programming");

        System.out.println(name);
    }
}
